(23, 'Our Successful betting strategy', NULL, '<p>Both teams to score is a popular betting method, but many people get it wrong when picking out potential BTTS matches. We&#39;ve come up with a simple strategy to use, this has a high success rate and we&#39;re sharing it to you for free.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s not as simple as picking the top teams to all score against each other, there&#39;s been plenty of examples where these matches have ended in a bore draw or only one side scoring the goals. In fact, for our betting strategy&nbsp;the league table only plays a small part for when we are picking out our matches, we compare stats, h2h and we do have a quick look at the league table too.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We at Football-today.co.uk have actually made it easier for you to compare the stats and h2h. Simply click on any fixture and you will see the team stats and h2h, see the picture below. (We tipped this match on twitter and as you can see it ended 2-1 recently)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://football-today.co.uk/uploads/b6b94a7087e3072dbb845fa90c63d5ed.JPG\" style=\"height:345px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This strategy is pretty simple once you understand, you simply look at the two teams and compare the stats. So for example&nbsp;KFUM Oslo were&nbsp;playing at home and as you can see they scored on average 1.8 goals whilst conceding 1.2 goals. So from this you expect them to score at least 1 goal since they average almost 2 goals.&nbsp;Fredrikstad&nbsp;when playing away scored and conceded on average 1.7 goals. In total Fredrikstad scored 2.1 goals on average per game. So what we can take from this is we expect Fredrikstad to score also and are likely to concede as they concede over 1 goal on average.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key is to look for matches with high average numbers so remember if the team is playing at home it&#39;s important to look at the home stats and&nbsp;if the team is playing away you look at the away stats.We also take a look at the head to head. The higher the number the better, it&#39;s that simple and very easy to do. We&#39;ve been doing this for a long time and it&#39;s very successful.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '7f3795e116fd86748b7f860e7da15cdc.JPEG', '', 0, 0, 4, '2021-09-17 04:57:12', '2024-02-02 19:00:36', 0),
