(587, 'LiveFootballToday - New and upcoming changes', NULL, '<p>Introduction -&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It has been chaotic these last couple of months regrading changes to the site, However we are finally making positive progress with the changes. In this article we will talk about the big changes that have happened and we&#39;ll discuss some future changes. We also would like to take this opportunity to thank everyone for their support.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New homepage -&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The big talking point is the new homepage. We feel this is a huge improvement even though this isn&#39;t 100% complete just yet. There&#39;s still some finishing touches to do regarding the design and we&#39;ll be adding some filter options eventually.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you click on a fixture now, the fixture itself will expand rather then opening a new page. First you will see a little summary of each sides form and h2h records along with the prediction. You can view this on almost every match. The next tab is match centre, which is basic at the moment but does the job. Lineups is the final tab on that section and&nbsp;we&#39;ll be creating some formations graphics to go with it along with ingame player stats.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you click match preview, a further 3 tabs will appear. The first tab being summary which has the recent fixtures, h2h and league table. The net tab is team stats which has seen a big improvement. We are now offering stats that cover almost everything. From anything from tackels to corners,&nbsp;we have the important stats covered.&nbsp;The player stats have remained the same however, we will be adding more player stats to this tab in due course.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>League pages and club page -&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These pages have remained the same however some of these features are worth checking out, such as the team stats comparisons on the league page and you view each club transfers on each club pages. These pages will be improved in due course, but the focus currently is the quality of the stats and data we have to offer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Ads are annoying, we all hate them. However, we have taken the decision to use them as small revenue stream to help keep livefootballtoday going and to continue to improve the website. We will be bringing the option in to hide ads for a small fee which is &pound;1 a month or you can subscribe for the year for &pound;10.00&nbsp;The stats we offer will always be free, nothing has changed on that front. We aim to be the go to place for reliable stats and data. Whether you&#39;re a punter or just enjoy looking at the stats and data, we will have you covered! We have some amazing new features linedup&nbsp;including a couple of new pages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'e1607e8d073999e406ed8e76063e3c30.png', '', 0, 0, 4, '2023-12-28 10:50:59', '2023-12-28 13:12:19', 0),
(588, 'LiveFootballToday  - 60% club', NULL, '<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Introduction </strong>- In this guide we have explained how we pick matches for our 60% club.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>60% club</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 60% club is a name given to a strategy that use and&nbsp;that we post on X (twitter). It&#39;s important that we inform you now that we only select the home team for this. In order to help us pick these matches we first take a look at the results form, attacking form and defensive form. In an ideal world we would like the home side to come out on top on all 3 of these factors. Form is very important, if you have the momentum going into the game there&#39;s a greater chance you&#39;ll get a result.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We then take a look at what the h2h says, if this is against us i.e the away side has a 60% or more then we tend to avoid this game. This is because h2h games do play a psychological part in football, if one team dominates the h2h then they have a great chance of winning even if they are in bad form. Sometimes if the away team h2h percentage is between 50-59% we may still select this match as this doesn&#39;t&nbsp;prove dominance in the past meetings. If this is the case we manually take a look at the past meetings on the match preview tab to help us decide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The higher percentage of Poisson Distribution for the home side the better really. We like to make sure that the home side has at least 50% for this. Finally that leaves the win percentage, we only pick games where the home side has 60% chance or greater to win the game. If the win percentage if 59.9% we still don&#39;t pick this match. Nothing less then 60%, you have to be consistent and disciplined. Once we find a game where these factors are met we then click on the match preview tab on that game to do our own quick research. We have made it very easy for you to do this. On on the overview tab we have recent results, h2h record and the league table. Then we have the team stats tabs which displays each team overall stats and the home team - home stats and the away team - away stats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If we notice that the away side is either considerably higher in the table or seems to dominate when playing away then we tend too take a pass on the match&nbsp;as there is more uncertainty in it. We never go by the odds, sometimes the odds could&nbsp;low for example 1.20, other times there may be plenty of value and the odds being 1.90 or even higher.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Conclusion </strong>- We&#39;re more than happy to offer you assistance, so pop us a message on X if you require help. If you give this a go, then do&nbsp;let us know how you get on!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '8a1e5c63f218a5733faf4c448a6d7714.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 18, '2024-01-16 07:53:18', '2024-03-03 06:32:07', 0),
