(622, 'Managing your bankroll', NULL, '<p><strong>Managing Your Betting Bankroll</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bets won&#39;t always win, but if you place odds of about 10/1 on average, and win 1 in every 9 you&#39;ll be in long-term profit. Or if you place odds of EVENS and win 2 from 3 on average you will be in profit. Ultimately, you need to make a gain over time, and it certainly doesn&#39;t happen overnight. That&#39;s why you need to manage your bankroll.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accas can be all-day fun, or disappoint&nbsp;you after 45 mins of the 1st leg... no room for&nbsp;getting emotional! That&#39;s why you need a plan. It can be annoying when you lose 3 singles, especially when the stats pre-game looked strong, and you just lost a small chunk of your bankroll. For all of the above reasons, it is important that you stick to a plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key is to enjoy the bets and not expect that they win. Understand that whilst bookies get things wrong sometimes, and you can find value, if a bet is priced at 22/1 that means your chances are that you win 1 in 23 bets. Obviously, we aim to break that trend and profit, and not everyone can do it. That&#39;s how bookies make their profits, and there&#39;s lots of them out there so it must be a formula that works for them in general.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The other reason people choose to bet is to add some entertainment to a sporting event that they are already interested in. For example, it can make watching a game even more intense if you have some added interest via a bet. You may be urging on one last corner as well as waiting for the result, or hoping there is a goal before half time, etc. Remember that this is meant to be enjoyable, not stressful. If you feel it becoming a stress, a need, or even an addiction: take stock and review what you actually want from it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Choosing your bankroll:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Work out what you can afford first of all, and by that this means &#39;What you can afford TO LOSE&#39;. If you begin knowing that the risk is the total loss of this amount, then you are more comfortable in the unfortunate event that this happens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Work out your anticipated losses as part of selecting the bankroll. If you&#39;re following a tipster then they may do this for you, however, over time if you&#39;re doing your own bets you&#39;ll begin to be able to understand your strike rate (how many bets you win vs how many you lose). Once you know this, you can kind of predict how things might go.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is recommended that you have one approach for your serious bets, and then a separate amount for your fun bets, or for those you choose to follow from other people. Lots of other bets = bad news. If one tipster is in form is making you money, and you follow 9 others, if the other 9 are losing then you are likely not making any money overall, and most probably losing! It&#39;s easy to get drawn into seeing huge winning slips, though many of these tipsters are not posting and shouting about their losses in the same way, for sure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For serious bets</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>operate on a points/bank system</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This approach helps you to stick to bets you can afford. Take the amount of money you are able to allocate to your bets, and divide by the bank points in order to establish your stake per point.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: the start&nbsp;bank for the service offered is 50 points, or you have reviewed your betting and think you need 50x your normal stake to stay afloat. You have &pound;100 which you can afford to bet. Your stake per bet would be... &pound;2 (100 / 50 = 2)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stick to that staking plan and change only with strict rules. Some reasons to adapt the bankroll are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The&nbsp;service yields a profit which you wish to re-invest:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example:&nbsp;the service turns your start bank of &pound;100 into &pound;150. You may wish to draw out the profit and&nbsp;maintain&nbsp;the &pound;2 stake, continue with the current stake, or you may wish to revise the stake to &pound;3 per bet (&pound;150 / 50 = 3) as this would now be affordable. If you&#39;re planning to do this, don&#39;t adjust stakes daily, you need to select a time period for review e.g. monthly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Your disposable income changes:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: it&#39;s payday, and you have an extra&nbsp;&pound;100 that you would like to add to your portfolio. You may choose a second service with the same start bank, and operate 2 services at &pound;2 per stake, or you may choose to increase your bank to &pound;200, and can therefore allocate &pound;4 per stake (200 / 50 = 4). Pay your bills first! Betting is not guaranteed, that&#39;s why it is called gambling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>You / your service experiences a losing run (it happens from time to time).</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: In the same way that you would increase stakes (if you wished) with an increase in income or profit, you should also consider revising your staking plan if the service experiences a decline that impacts your start bank. If you only had &pound;50 left, you could choose to ride it out in the hope that fortunes turn, or you could reduce your stake to &pound;1, meaning you were still operating with a 50 point bank (50 / 50 = 1).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Follow the staking plan:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The theory is you&#39;re only betting what you can afford, and losses don&#39;t cause you alarm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See an illustration in the table below to further demonstrate how to set your staking plan:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:390px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Start Bank (points)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Start Bank (&pound;; $; etc.)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Stake&nbsp;(&pound;; $; etc.) per point</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>50</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>150</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>50</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>50</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>100</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>500</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>5</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>100</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>750</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>7.5</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>150</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>500</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3.33</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '15b0a092e90639e212ca9e1c7d00da4b.png', 'free', 0, 0, 18, '2024-02-05 09:05:52', '2024-02-06 07:11:43', 1),
(623, 'Premier league review 05-02-24', NULL, '<p><big><strong>Introduction </strong></big>- In the article we have left 3 match reviews and at the bottom of the article you can see how our predictions did. (hint - Very good)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><big><strong>Match Review</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Everton 2 - 2 Tottenham -&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Corners: Everton&#39;s Dominance in Set Pieces</strong> The match witnessed a flurry of corners, with a total of 14, and Everton asserting their dominance in this aspect with 9 corners. Set pieces proved to be a crucial avenue for both teams, with each corner adding an element of excitement and a potential shift in momentum.&nbsp;<strong>Shots on Target: Clinical Finishing</strong> The accuracy in front of goal was evident, with a total of 11 shots on target. Tottenham led in this department with 6 shots on target, showcasing their clinical finishing. Everton, however, demonstrated their offensive prowess by testing the opposing goalkeeper on 5 occasions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Current Standings:&nbsp;</strong>Everton finds themselves in a precarious 18th position, just one point away from the relegation zone. The draw represents a missed opportunity to climb to safety, adding pressure to secure points in upcoming fixtures.&nbsp;On the flip side, Tottenham sit 5th in the league, a mere two points adrift from&nbsp;a Champions League spot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Newcastle 4-4 Luton -&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Possession Battle and Offensive Onslaught:</strong> Newcastle enjoyed slightly more possession&nbsp;holding onto the ball for 54% of the match. This dominance in possession was translated into an offensive onslaught, resulting in a remarkable eight corners and six shots on target for the home side.&nbsp;&nbsp;Despite Newcastle&#39;s offensive prowess, Luton showcased clinical efficiency on the counter. With only two corners and six shots on target, Luton made the most of their opportunities, highlighting their ability to capitalize on limited possession.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Current Standings:</strong> The draw has implications for both teams in the league standings. Newcastle now finds themselves in the 9th position, a mere five points away from the coveted 5th place. As they sit comfortably in the top half, Newcastle will aim to build on this performance to close the gap and potentially secure a European qualification spot. Luton&#39;s sit&nbsp;in 17th place, just one point clear of the relegation zone, underscores the importance of every point in their fight for survival.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Arsenal 3-1 Liverpool -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Possession vs. Precision:</strong> Despite having just 43% possession, Arsenal&#39;s performance was characterized by clinical precision. With only 2 corners and 7 shots on target, Arsenal demonstrated their ability to capitalize on limited opportunities, turning possession into effective attacking plays.&nbsp;On the other hand, Liverpool showcased their trademark possession-based style with over 500 passes. However, the attacking prowess that usually accompanies their possession was stifled, reflected in their 10 shots with only 1 finding the target. Arsenal&#39;s defensive resilience played a crucial role in limiting Liverpool&#39;s usual free-flowing attacking game.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Impact on the League Standings:</strong> The result had significant implications for both teams in the league standings. Arsenal&#39;s win moved&nbsp;them to 2nd place, just 2 points adrift from the top of the league. The Gunners are now genuine contenders for the title, with their ability to secure crucial wins against fellow top-four teams.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><big><strong>Our predictions&nbsp;</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Everton vs Tottenham - Each team 3+ shots on target &amp; 7 match corners </li>\r\n	<li>Brighton vs Crystal Palace - Over 2.5 goals </li>\r\n	<li>Burnley vs Fulham - 9+ Corners </li>\r\n	<li>Newcastle vs Luton - Newcastle 6+ shots on target </li>\r\n	<li>Sheffield United vs Aston Villa - Over 2.5 goals </li>\r\n	<li>Bournemouth vs Nottingham Forest - Both teams to score </li>\r\n	<li>Chelsea vs Wolves - 9&nbsp;or more match corners </li>\r\n	<li>Manchester United vs West Ham - 40 + match booking points </li>\r\n	<li>Arsenal vs Liverpool - Both teams to score </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><big><strong>Conclusion:&nbsp;</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sign up now for<strong> just &pound;1.00 per month&nbsp;</strong>to access our expert predictions! Our team experts assesses every match, providing you with winning insights that can elevate your betting game. Don&#39;t miss out on the chance to turn predictions into profits.&nbsp;</p>', 'acc60730da99d19d748342b8f75593b0.jpg', 'free', 0, 0, 20, '2024-02-05 11:23:36', '2024-02-05 12:17:43', 1);
