(682, 'Preview & Predictions', NULL, '<p><big><strong>Introduction </strong></big>-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s been an extremely disappointing month and as a result we are in the red this month, and it&#39;s very unlikely we&#39;ll end the month in profit, but we will give it our best go! We have four predictions for today, we&#39;ve explained below how we have played these.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><big><strong>Matches:&nbsp;</strong></big></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jong AZ vs NAC</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Preview:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Going into this game Jong AZ have the far better form winning 3 times from their last 5 games where as NAC are actually without a win in 5 games drawing 3 times and losing twice and as a result they have dropped down the table but a win could see them overtake Jong AZ. The h2h favours the NAC today which will give them a boost.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Jong AZ have scored an average of 1.8 home goals&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>NAC have scored an average of 1.9 away goals&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Both sides average over 10 shots per game&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Prediction - Both teams to score&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Al-Ettifaq vs&nbsp;Al-Hilal Saudi FC:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Preview:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Going into this game the hosts have struggled lately and have lacked wins. Todays prediction on this match is heavily persuaded by each sides form and the strengths of the visitors&nbsp;This could quite easily be a 0-3 win for Al-Hilal today, this is down to their ability to score 3 or more goals per game.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Al-Ettifaq have just 1 win from last 5 games and have 3 wins from 9 home games</li>\r\n	<li>Al-Ettifaq have kept just 1 home clean sheet&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Al-Hilal Saudi FC&nbsp; sit top of league winning all 5 off their last 5 league games&nbsp;</l