(695, 'Preview & predictions 06-03-24', NULL, '<h3><strong>Introduction</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We have another 3 predictions for tonight, we&#39;re playing all these as singles but also have staked them as a treble, We just need 2 singles to land to make a small profit, but of course we hope all 3 win!</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Matches:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Middlesbrough vs Norwich</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The host Middlesbrough are out of form with just 1 win from their last 5 games, results haven&#39;t gone their&nbsp;way either and despite sitting 4th they are just 6 points above the relegation zone. The visitors Norwich come into this game unbeaten in their last 5 games with three wins. In Norwich last match they beat Sunderland 1-0 and as a result they sit 7th in the league. In Middlesbrough last match they lost 2-0 against Stoke City. When these sides met back in October the game ended 1-2 Middlesbrough.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Middlesbrough have scored an average of 1.0&nbsp; goals whilst conceding an average of 1.2&nbsp;goals at home.</li>\r\n	<li>Middlesbrough have kept just 5 clean sheets from 17 games.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Norwich have scored an average of 1.6 goals whilst conceding an average of 1.9 goals when playing away.</li>\r\n	<li>Norwich have kept 1 clean sheet from 17 away games.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Prediction: Both teams to score&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Watford vs Swansea</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Watford have to be careful not to be drawn into a relegation battle, despite sitting 12th they are just 6 points clear and have just 1 win from their last 5 games losing 4 time. Swansea sit 15th and are just 4 points above the drop zone thanks to 3 wins in their last 5 games. In Watford last match they lost 1-0 against Millwall whilst in Swansea last match they beat Blackburn 2-1 at home. Watford have scored at least 1 goal in each of their last 5 games whilst Swansea have scored at least 1 goal in 4 matches from their last 5.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Watford have scored an average of 1.6 goals whilst conceding an average of 1.4 goals at home.</li>\r\n	<li>Watford have kept 5 clean sheets form 17 matches.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Swansea have scored an average of 1.5 goals whilst conceding an average of 1.8 goals when playing away.</li>\r\n	<li>Swansea have kept just 3 clean sheets from 17 away games.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Prediction: Both teams to score</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cardiff vs Huddersfield</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hosts Cardiff have hit some form and are unbeaten in 3 games, winning twice. But before that, they did lose twice in a row so they have found some form at the right time as they sit 9 points above the drop zone, things couldn&#39;t been different.. Huddersfield are 21st above Stoke on goal difference, and like Cardiff, Huddersfield have found some form with 2 wins and 1 draw from their last 5 games. Cardiff beat Bristol City 0-1 in their last match whilst Huddersfield drew 1-1 against Leeds.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cardiff have scored an average of 1.2 goals whilst conceding an average of 1.2 goals at home&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Cardiff have kept 5 clean sheet from 17 games.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Huddersfield have scored an average of 1.1 goals whilst conceding an average of 1.9 goals when playing away.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Huddersfield&nbsp;have kept just 1 clean sheet from 17 away games.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">Prediction: Both teams to score&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Conclusion:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Each prediction has been fully researched as always but do fee