(718, 'Preview & Predictions 23-03-24', NULL, '<h1><small><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>During the international break, we don&#39;t bet for the sake of it, it&#39;s nice to use this opportunity to have a little break away from betting and recharge. We&#39;re back today with 3 predictions, we have played these as 3 singles as well as a joint treble. We need just 2 singles to land to make a profit.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><strong>Matches</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Burton vs Port Vale</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whilst scoring goals might not spring to your mind when you see these two sides, they do concede plenty of goals and with the match importance I would expect both teams will be going for the win and with them already being vulnerable at the back we could well see a few goals. Burton have been in poor form losing 3 league matches in a row and have 4 defeats and 1 draw from their last 5 league games. Port Vale on the other hand have slightly. better form, by that I mean they have picked up just 1 more point from their last 5 league games with 3 defeats and 2 draws. The hosts Burton do sit higher up in the table with them sitting 19th on 39 points whilst Port Vale are 23rd on 33 points.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Burton have conceded an average of 1.2 goals when playing at home keeping 4 clean sheets from 18 home games.</li>\r\n	<li>Port Vale have conceded an average of 0.8 goals when playing away keeping 4 clean sheets from 18 away games.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Burton average 3 shots on target and average 11 total shots at home.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Port Vale average 5 shots on target and average 15 match shots when playing away.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px\">Prediction: Both teams to score</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Morecambe vs Gillingham&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just two points separate these sides with the hosts Morecambe sitting 12th on 54 points meanwhile Gillingham sit 10th and&nbsp;are on&nbsp;56 points. Gillingham are just 1 point behind 7th place AFC Wimbledon, meaning Morecambe are 3 points behind 7th place., With both of these sides battling for a play off spot, we could be in for a highly competitive match with a few goals. The hosts have lost their last 3 league games and will be looking to make things right today whilst Gillingham have had 1 defeat and 2 draws from their last 3 games, so they also will want a win today. When these sides met back in September it ended Gillingham 2-1 Morecambe.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Morecambe have scored an average of 1.3 goals whilst conceding an average of 1.1 goals at home keeping 6 clean sheets from 18 home games.</li>\r\n	<li>Gillingham&nbsp;have scored on average 0.8 goals whilst conceding on average 1.3 goals when playing away keeping 7 clean sheets.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Morecambe average 3 shots on target at home with a total of 11 shots.</li>\r\n	<li>Gillingham average 4 shots on target when playing away whilst averaging 14 total shots on the road.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px\">Prediction: Both teams to score&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Stockport vs MK Dons&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A huge game in league 2 in which both teams want automatic promotion to league 1. At the moment it&#39;s the hosts who are looking more likely with Stockport sitting 2nd and are on 68 points. Whilst MK Dons do sit 4th in league 2, they are just 1 point behind Stockport County.. Stockport haven&#39;t had many wins lately but are unbeaten from their last 5 league game with 4 draws and 1 win meanwhile MK Dons have picked up 3 wins and 2 defeats from their last 5 league games, When these sides met back in September int ended MK Doms 1-2 Stockport County.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key stats:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Stockport County have scored an average if 1.9 goals at home and average 5 shots on target at home whilst averaging 15 total shots per home game.</li>\r\n	<li>MK Dons average 1.3 goals on the road this season in the league whilst averaging 5 shots on target and 15 total shots when playing away.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px\">Prediction: Both teams to score</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><small><strong>Conclusion</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>There is plenty of value on offer with these predictions, it was hard to avoid them. Whilst the stats aren&#39;t as solid as wed like, the form and the importance of each game will have a bigger influence. If you&#39;re not confident then do feel free to conduct some research yourself. Please bet responsibly.&nbsp;</p>', '78477051dd8413b6edbb36ba776ee44a.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 19, '2024-03-21 17:56:51', '2024-03-22 18:33:29', 1),
(719, 'Sweden Allsvenskan season preview and predictions', NULL, '<p><strong>Introduction:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a new season right around the corner, we have done a preview on some teams to look out for going into the new campaign as well as out season bets..&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Four teams for goals?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Last season these four teams scored 40 or more goals and conceded 39&nbsp;or more goals each.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hammarby&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Sirius&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>IFK Norrkoping&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>IF Brommapojkarna&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking at the season ahead I will be relying on these sides for goals, whether that is the over/under market or both teams to score. I believe we will see plenty of value with these sides this season. This does not mean I will be backing goals in every match these sides play. I will still be taking form and stats into the equation. Over the course of the season one or more of these sides might be replaced if they aren&#39;t finding the net.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>To win the league -&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>My pick is probably the most obvious choice &#39;which is Malmo&#39; to win the league. I am getting odds over 2.10 on this with William&nbsp;&nbsp; hill and I believe this is fantastic value. The reason the odds are high is because Malmo won the league on the last day of the season beating Elfsborg&nbsp;1-0 who before the match were top of the league.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I don&#39;t think Elfsborg will do as well this season now they have European football to shift their attention too. Although this doesn&#39;t start for another couple of months this could be a distraction to them. When they finally start their European journey, their players will tire rather quick and you&#39;ll see this having a negative impact on the league form.&nbsp;The majority of Malmo players will be able to perform well in league and cup. The only other 