ous season but finished 6th place, however they were level on points with the team in 5th place.&nbsp;This time Kalmar had 45 points but still managed 13 wins.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Final say</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It really could go either way for Kalmar, I think they will be worth keeping an eye on. They will either shine or have a freefall season. Kalmar came so close to relegation twice and close to a dream top 3 finish 2 seasons ago. William hill are offering a great market with their outrights. You can place Kalmar to win the league and place this as each way. William Hill are paying 3 places at 1/5 of the price. Please only stake your loose change.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>Conclusion:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To conclude, here are our two pre season bets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Malmo to win the league (Each way paying 3 places) If Malmo finish 2nd or 3rd we will see some of the stake returned.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Kalmar win the league (Each way paying 3 places) A 3rd place finish will result in profit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regarding the four teams we have picked for goals, we will be keeping a close eye on these sides fixtures throughout the season, more so at the start of the season as we should see some value in the odds.&nbsp;</p>', '13b3198634c4e0a1da90b36b41715eed.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 25, '2024-03-24 18:03:54', '2024-03-27 05:44:45', 1),
(720, 'Norway Eliteserien season preview & Predictions', NULL, '<p><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article we have left our outright winner/s as well as certain teams to look out for and hopefully ou can rely on these teams for goals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>A Winning Strategy with Bodo/Glimt and Molde?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since the 2019 season, the Norwegian league has witnessed a dominance shared between two formidable teams: Bodo/Glimt and Molde. This consistency not only underscores the strength of these clubs but also presents a golden opportunity for us to capitalise on their continued success. What makes this opportunity even more enticing is the fact that, with the current odds available, we stand to profit regardless of which side win the league.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Here&#39;s how:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Bodo/Glimt odds of 2.10 to win the league, a calculated &pound;100.00 stake could yield returns of &pound;210, meaning you&#39;d make a profit of&nbsp;&pound;110. Meanwhile, Molde, with odds of 4.0, offers an equally promising prospect, where a &pound;50 stake&nbsp;returns of &pound;200, securing a profit of &pound;150.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If we place these stakes on each bet we&#39;d make a profit regardless which team wins the league. Here why:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using the stake example above We have a total stake of &pound;150 and each bet returns &pound;200 or more therefore we would make a profit should one of these sides win the league.&nbsp;If Bodo wins the league we&#39;d make &pound;60.00 where as if Molde wins the league we&#39;d make &pound;50.00. It&#39;s a risk, this is not financial advice, this is just what we&#39;re doing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Four teams for goals?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These four teams scored and conceded 46 or more goals last season.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Viking - 61/48</li>\r\n	<li>Sarpsborg - 55/52</li>\r\n	<li>Rosenborg - 46/50</li>\r\n	<li>Sandefjord - 47/55</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking at the season ahead I will be relying on these sides for goals, whether that is the over/under market or both teams to score. I believe we will see plenty of value with these sides this season. This does not mean I will be backing goals in every match these sides play. I will still be taking form and stats into the equation. Over the course of the season one or more of these sides might be replaced if they aren&#39;t finding the net.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Summary:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To conclude we have two outright bets with that being Bodo to win the league &amp; Molde to win the league. These sides aren&#39;t guarantee to win the league, they are jus the two favourites.&nbsp;Regarding the four teams we have picked for goals, we will be keeping a close eye on these sides fixtures throughout the season, more so at the start of the season as we should see some value in the odds.&nbsp;</p>', '58206904774c83da08ba7181dd1e728e.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 25, '2024-03-26 07:15:20', '2024-03-27 05:44:54', 1),
(721, 'Our Swedish league strategy', NULL, '<h1><small><strong>Our Sweden leagues strategy:</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The Swedish leagues Allsvensken and Superatten are reliable for home wins, this is backed up by data from previous seasons. Taking the data into account, we will be focusing on home wins in the Swedish leagues.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will be looking for odds of 1.50 or more, higher odds the better as this could mean more value and more profit. If we can manage to find 3 teams a week, we&#39;d just need two to land in order for us to make a profit, This is a basic, and similar strategy to what we have used before, but it is a reliable one. As tempting as it may be we won&#39;t be picking anymore than 3 matches per week, discipline&nbsp;is key.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to do thi strategy successful, you must stake the same amount on each single. Af the end/start of each month, this is when to review your stake, if you&#39;re losing money perhaps lower the stakes, if you&#39;re winning and feeling confident perhaps increase the stake.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><small><strong>How to find the teams to win?</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Whilst there&#39;s no guarantee way to find teams that will 100% win, the research you do is vital. Remember to look for form and The hosts home stats and the visitors away stats. We are currently working on an advance new feature that will make picking teams so much easier and hopefully rewarding!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Top 3&nbsp;tips:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Form</strong> - Once a few games have past, ideally you&#39;d like to look for teams where the home side has lost at least 1 match in recent times but ideally have more wins. This is because, eventually a team is going to lose, how often do you see teams winning 5 games in a row? It&#39;s rare, and puts more pressure on the hosts, things like complacency will influence the result.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Stats </strong>- How does the home side do when they play at home, are they a fortress at home? Do the visitors struggle on the road and find it hard to score? Just because the away side could be higher up in the table, they could struggle when playing away. So check the home and away stats!&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>h2h </strong>- Does one team dominate the h2h meetings? Some teams just do perform better when playing that one team. Bogey teams are real, and you have to keep an eye out for that. That being said, do remember to check the date of the past matches, as I think it&#39;s fair to say if the last meeting was 5 years ago, it&#39;s unlikely that will have any influence in today times.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><small><strong>Conclusion:</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>A basic but rewarding little strategy that we will be bringing you throughout the summer. If you haven&#39;t already, do check out our Swedish outrights&nbsp;</p>', '798178db38988dfb9cd360555cfb7849.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 24, '2024-03-27 06:15:30', '2024-03-28 19:12:29', 1),
