(798, 'Dortmund vs Real Madrid - Champions league Preview & Prediction 01-06-24', NULL, '<h1><small><strong>Introduction</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Borussia Dortmund face a formidable challenge as they go up against Real Madrid, who are aiming for their 15th Champions League title. Can Dortmund, the underdogs, overcome the odds and emerge victorious?</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><small><strong>Road to the Final</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Borussia Dortmund:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Round of 16:</strong> Dortmund overcame PSV with a 3-1 aggregate victory. After a 1-1 draw in the first leg at PSV, they secured their spot in the quarterfinals with a strong performance in the second leg.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Quarterfinals:</strong> Dortmund faced a setback in the first leg against Atletico Madrid, losing 2-1. However, they staged a remarkable comeback in the second leg with a 4-2 win, advancing with a 5-4 aggregate score.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Semifinals:</strong> Dortmund displayed consistent form, winning both legs against PSG 1-0 to secure their place in the final.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Real Madrid:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Round of 16:</strong> Real Madrid had a tough battle against RB Leipzig, winning the first leg 1-0 and drawing the second leg 1-1 to advance.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Quarterfinals:</strong> Madrid&#39;s encounter with Manchester City was intense, with a 3-3 draw in the first leg followed by a 1-1 draw in the second leg. Real Madrid advanced after winning 4-3 on penalties.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Semifinals:</strong> Madrid faced Bayern Munich, drawing 2-2 in the first leg and winning the second leg 2-1 to book their spot in the final.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1><strong><small>Lets take a look at some historic results:</small></strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Underdogs Prevailing:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In 2004, FC Porto, managed by Jos&eacute; Mourinho, won the Champions League against expec