(804, 'ITS COMING HOME - Euro 2024 England preview', NULL, '<h1><small><strong>Euros Preview: England&#39;s Prospects</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Recent friendly matches have highlighted some weaknesses in the England squad, with defeats against Brazil and Iceland and a draw against Belgium. However, if Gareth Southgate can glean the right insights from these games, this could turn into a positive. Dominating teams with 5-0 victories in the past hasn&#39;t always served England well, leading to complacency in major tournaments. This dose of reality offers an excellent opportunity for growth. Additionally, lowered expectations might actually reduce the pressure, with opponents potentially underestimating England&#39;s capabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><small><strong>Group Stage Expectations</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>In their group, England are expected to emerge victorious in all three games, although no disrespect is meant to the other nations. Denmark poses the toughest challenge, boasting some talented players, particularly in attack. Serbia, on the other hand, have struggled recently, suffering a 4-0 defeat to Russia in March and narrowly beating Cyprus 1-0. Slovenia could be a dark horse, having secured an impressive 2-0 victory against Portugal in March.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While a maximum of 9 points is achievable for England, 7 points would still be a satisfactory outcome, provided the team progresses without significant injuries. The key to a successful tournament lies in maintaining player fitness and avoiding burnout during the group stages. Narrow 2-1 wins are acceptable as long as the squad remains in top condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1><small><strong>Players to Watch</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eberechi Eze</strong>: Eze is a versatile player who can operate in midfield or on the wings. His ability to drive the ball forward, create chances, and surprise opponents with his unpredictability makes him a valuable asset. Even if he doesn&#39;t start, his impact as a substitute could be crucial in changing the dynamics of a game.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bukayo Saka</strong>: Saka is poised for a standout tournament. With his pace and skill, he can cause significant problems for opposition defenses. Despite being only 22, Saka has experience from the last Euros and the World Cup, which should help him handle the pressure. The supporting cast around him, including the creativity of Phil Foden, the strength of Harry Kane, and the brilliance of Jude Bellingham, will enhance his performance. If Saka plays on the right, his combination with Kyle Walker could be particularly devastating, offering pace and overlapping runs that will trouble any defense.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><small><strong>Verdict:</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Realistically, England have the potential to win the tournament. The squad boasts impressive depth and a lethal attacking lineup. There is a great balance of experienced players and young talent eager to shine on the European stage. Has Southgate learnt from his past mistakes?&nbsp;Will England play to their strenghts?&nbsp;&nbsp;&#39;Bring it home lads&#39; will become a reality if so.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '4e09e418d491e559ba968a7e95f517bb.png', 'free', 0, 0, 23, '2024-06-08 10:46:11', '2024-06-13 04:34:34', 1),
(805, 'Preview & Predictions 09-06-24', NULL, '<h1><small><strong>Introduction:&nbsp;</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>A great day yesterday winning both of our trebles, even better if you combined the two trebles into a six fold! Today we have another two trebles:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><small><strong>Predictions</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Norway treble&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Brattvag vs Vard - Over 2.5 goals&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Viking II vs Notodden - Home win</li>\r\n	<li>Orn Horten vs Lysekloster - Over 2.5 goals</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sweden treble&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Karlskrona vs Hegaborgs - Home win</li>\r\n	<li>Laholm vs Landvetter - Over 2.5 goals&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Skovde vs IK Gauthiod - Home win</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><small><strong>Conclusion:</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Whilst it would e great if we can land both trebles like yesterday, we just need 1 to land to secure a small profit. Bet responsibly and good luck!&nbsp;</p>', 'b86560be27590f0ae1b43f46e5c4f468.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 19, '2024-06-09 05:28:34', '2024-06-09 08:02:18', 1),
(806, 'Euro 2024 Outrights & predictions', NULL, '<h1><small><strong>Introduction:</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>With the euro 2024 starting today we have shared our outright bets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1><small><strong>Winners:</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>England @ 4/1 | 5.0 - Each way.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">England come into this tournament favorites and on paper they should really be lifting the trophy. With the quality and depth the team has, they should be achieving far more than what is currently being achieved to say the least. Some of the players and manager experienced defeat in the euro 2020 final, have they learned&nbsp;from that? Time will tell. Going forward England have the capabilities to outscore any nation in this competition, is &#39;football coming home&#39; at last?</div>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1><small><strong>Group winners - Treble</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Group C - England&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">If England are to go on and be champions then you would expect 3 wins from 3 from their group. Denmark are seen as England biggest threat, and have caused upsets in the past. That beig said, if England are at their best then they shouldn&#39;t have any problems.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Group D - France&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">We could well see a surprise or two&nbsp;in this group as&nbsp;France are joined by Netherlands, Austria and Poland. Netherlands are seen as France biggest challenge and Poland could well be a &#39;dark horse&#39; in this group. That being said, when you look at the quality you would expect France to get at least 7 points and finish top of the group.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Group E - Belgium&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee;border:1px solid #cccccc;padding:5px 10px;\">This group is a fairly even group as you have 3 sides that are similar qualities, with them being Ukraine, Slovakia and Romania. Despite Belgium&nbsp;&#39;golden era&#39; have aged, you can&#39;t jut ignore some of the qualities they have, whilst they might not win all 3 games, I would expect the other teams not seeing results go their way.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h1><small><strong>Conclusion -&nbsp;</strong></small></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s so easy to get carried away in hope and have about 20 different outright bets. We have staked more on the group winners treble, meaning we will make a profit should just the treble land.&nbsp;Bet responsibly and good luck!&nbsp;</p>', '533a473edd6a49d3c7131216f6bd1951.png', 'paid', 0, 0, 19, '2024-06-13 04:50:17', '2024-06-14 04:40:38', 1);
